2026-01-12 16:37:01.837 | INFO     | rca.baseline.rag_tool_multicandidate_agent.controller:control_loop:230 - controller RAG Cluster 3 result: [{'content': 'Component: currencyservice-0\nEvent: currencyservice-0 failure at 2022-03-20 16:31:44\nSystem Type: Banking Microservice (pod)\nSymptoms: container network packet corruption; A critical log anomaly was detected in `shippingservice-2` at 16:32:00 UTC+8: `"warning envoy config StreamAggregatedResources gRPC config stream closed: <:content:>i/o timeout"`. This indicates the E; The Metric Mesh Anomaly Report shows a large number of Istio-related metric anomalies starting at 16:31:00 UTC+8, coinciding with the failure time. These anomalies were widespread across many services; Anomalies such as `istio_request_bytes.http.500.` (seen on `currencyservice-2`) and `istio_tcp_connections_closed.UH` (No healthy upstream hosts, seen on `adservice2-0`) are direct consequences of ser\nAffected Metrics: CPU, HTTP, I/O, TCP, connection, gRPC, memory, network, rr, rt, sr, trace\nRoot Cause Category: The incident was caused by network packet corruption at the container level for the `currencyservice-0` pod, as stated in the ground truth. This low-l\nFailure Pattern: The incident was caused by network packet corruption at the container level for the `currencyservice-0` pod, as stated in the ground truth. This low-level network fault disrupted the pod\'s Istio sidecar proxy, leading to communication failures. The evidence strongly suggests this manifested as a loss of connectivity between the sidecar and the Istio control plane, causing I/O timeouts. This initial failure had a cascading effect, resulting in widespread service mesh anomalies, including HTTP 500 errors and connection failures, as other services attempted to communicate with the affected pod or experienced similar network degradation.\nMitigation Principles: 1. Investigate the underlying Container Network Interface (CNI) plugin and the host kernel\'s networking stack o